title: Continuous Time Bayesian Networks
abstract: In this paper we present a language for finite state continuous time Bayesian networks (CTBNs), which describe structured stochastic processes that evolve over continuous time.  The state of the system is decomposed into a set of local variables whose values change over time.  The dynamics of the system are described by specifying the behavior of each local variable as a function of its parents in a directed (possibly cyclic) graph.  The model specifies, at any given point in time, the distribution over two aspects: when a local variable changes its value and the next value it takes.
